LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 315, As Amended
BY REVENUE AND TAXATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TAXATION; AMENDING SECTION 63-3622VV, IDAHO CODE, TO REVISE PRO-
3 VISIONS REGARDING THE IDAHO INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY EQUIPMENT SALES TAX
4 EXEMPTION; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 63-3622VV, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
7 hereby amended to read as follows:
8 63-3622VV. IDAHO INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY EQUIPMENT. (1) On and after
9 July 1, 2020, and before March 1, 2025, there is exempted from the taxes
10 imposed by this chapter the purchase or use of eligible server equipment
11 and new data center facilities, as defined in this section. The exemption
12 provided in this section shall be available only to qualifying business
13 entities and contractors installing eligible server equipment or building
14 new data center facilities for qualifying business entities. On and after
15 March 1, 2025, the exemption provided in this section shall only be available
16 for the time period provided in subsection (2)(k) of this section and shall
17 be subject to the provisions of subsection (3) of this section; however,
18 such limitations shall not apply to any taxpayer that received the exemption
19 provided in this section before March 1, 2025. The exemption provided in
20 this section shall not be available for property that has been the subject of
21 business incentives granted to a taxpayer or its affiliates, pursuant to the
22 Idaho reimbursement incentive act, sections 67-4737 through 67-4744, Idaho
23 Code.
24 (2) As used in this section:
25 (a) "Business entity" means a separate legal entity or separately oper-
26 ated segment of business that exists for the primary purpose of engaging
27 in a commercial activity for profit and whose sole purpose is the oper-
28 ation of a data center. For the purposes of this section, a separately
29 operated segment of business is a segment of a business for which sep-
30 arate records are maintained and that is operated by an employee or em-
31 ployees whose primary employment responsibility is to operate the busi-
32 ness segment.
33 (b) "Cabling" means a fiber or copper cable used in data centers to con-
34 nect information sources to a server or storage device.
35 (c) "Capital investment" means real or tangible personal property that
36 is purchased for use in Idaho and is used by a business entity for the
37 purpose of operating a data center.
38 (d) "Chiller" means a cooling system used in data centers to remove heat
39 from an element and deposit it into another element.
40 (e) "Commencement of operations" means the date on which a certificate
41 of occupancy is issued for a data center.

2
1 (f) "Data center" means a facility comprised of one (1) or more build-
2 ings in Idaho that is used to house eligible server equipment for the
3 transmission and storage of data where the facility has the following
4 characteristics:
5 (i) Uninterruptible power supplies, generator power, or both;
6 (ii) Sophisticated fire suppression and prevention systems; and
7 (iii) Enhanced physical security and restricted access.
8 (g) "Eligible server equipment" means new server equipment acquired
9 by a qualifying business entity as described in this subsection that is
10 maintained and operated in a data center located in Idaho for the sole
11 purpose of data transmission and storage services, providing data and
12 transaction processing services, information technology services, or
13 computer collocation services. "Eligible server equipment" includes
14 servers, rack servers, chillers, storage devices, generators, cabling,
15 and enabling software integral to or installed on such equipment.
16 (h) "Generator" means an engine used in data centers to convert mechan-
17 ical energy into electricity.
18 (i) "New data center facilities" means buildings or structural com-
19 ponents of buildings, including equipment, materials, and fixtures
20 thereof, that are used in or intended for use primarily as a data center
21 in Idaho.
22 (j) "New jobs" means new jobs created in Idaho that are nonseasonal,
23 full-time jobs that collectively pay an average weekly wage that equals
24 or exceeds the average weekly wage for the county where the data center
25 is located, as determined by the most recent report of the United States
26 bureau of labor statistics. A job that merely changes locations within
27 the state of Idaho shall not be considered a new job under this section.
28 New jobs must exceed the business entity's highest number of full-time
29 employees in Idaho during the twenty-four (24) months immediately pre-
30 ceding the commencement of operations of the data center.
31 (k) "Qualifying business entity" means a business entity that certi-
32 fies to the state tax commission that it will make capital investments
33 in one (1) or more data centers after July 1, 2020, in amounts of at
34 least two hundred fifty million dollars ($250,000,000) in the aggre-
35 gate within the first five (5) years after commencement of construction
36 and that it will create and maintain at least thirty (30) new jobs at
37 the data center within two (2) calendar years after the commencement of
38 operations. Such business entities shall be entitled to a provisional
39 exemption pursuant to this section during the period in which they make
40 capital investments in data center property. If a business entity fails
41 to meet the investment and job creation requirements provided within
42 the time periods required in this section, it shall pay sales or use
43 taxes that would have been due if not for the granting of the provi-
44 sional exemption. If a business entity meets the investment and job
45 creation requirements provided within the time periods required in this
46 section, its provisional exemption shall become final without further
47 action, and thereafter the exemption shall also apply to all additional
48 purchases of eligible server equipment and purchases associated with
49 constructing new data center facilities. Any qualifying business en-
50 tity that has received the exemption provided in this section prior to

3
1 March 1, 2025, shall not be subject to exemption expiration after seven
2 (7) years as provided in this subsection. For any qualifying business
3 entity that receives this exemption after March 1, 2025, the exemption
4 shall expire seven (7) years from the date that the provisional exemp-
5 tion becomes final.
6 (l) "Rack server" means a computer in a data center dedicated to use as a
7 server and designed to be installed in a framework called a rack.
8 (m) "Server" means a computer or computer program used in data centers
9 that manages access to a centralized resource or service in a network.
10 (n) "Storage device" means a piece of computer equipment on which in-
11 formation can be stored and that is used in data centers.
12 (3) A qualifying business entity that receives an exemption pursuant to
13 this section on and after March 1, 2025, shall, for each year after the exemp-
14 tion expires after the time period provided in subsection (2)(k) of this sec-
15 tion, remit to the state tax commission sales tax on any item that would oth-
16 erwise be exempt if the qualifying business entity was continuing to claim
17 the exemption provided in this section. The state tax commission shall, on a
18 quarterly basis, transfer all such remitted funds to the tax relief fund es-
19 tablished pursuant to section 57-811, Idaho Code.
20 (3) (4) The state tax commission may promulgate rules to administer
21 and enforce the provisions of this section, including the promulgation of
22 rules relating to the provision of information necessary to certify that the
23 taxpayer satisfies the criteria for a qualifying business entity and to fa-
24 cilitate the remittance of taxes pursuant to subsection (3) of this section.
25 For the purpose of carrying out its duties to administer and enforce the
26 provisions of this section, the state tax commission shall have the powers
27 and duties provided by sections 63-217, 63-3038, 63-3039, 63-3042 through
28 63-3067, 63-3068, 63-3071, and 63-3074 through 63-3078, Idaho Code.
29 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
30 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after its
31 passage and approval.

